# 📈 StockSignal AI

A production-grade stock movement prediction system combining **PyTorch LSTM** neural networks with **FinBERT** sentiment analysis to forecast 5-day price direction across 7 major equities.

## Results

| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Test Accuracy | **62.07%** |
| Random Baseline | 50% |
| Academic Benchmark | 52-56% |
| Training Data | 7 stocks · 5 years |
| Features | 12 technical indicators |

## Key Finding

For high-volatility stocks like TSLA, the model learned that **technical indicators carry more predictive weight than news sentiment** — consistent with the *"buy the rumor, sell the news"* phenomenon observed in financial markets.

## Architecture
yfinance (5yr data)
↓
Technical Features (12):
Close, Volume, MA7, MA30, RSI,
MACD, StochRSI, BB_High, BB_Low,
Vol_MA7, Vol_MA30
+
FinBERT Sentiment Analysis
(financial news headlines → score)
↓
MinMaxScaler normalization
↓
Sliding window sequences (20 days)
↓
PyTorch LSTM (2-layer: 64→32 units)
↓
Direction (up/down) + Confidence score

## Model Performance By Ticker

| Ticker | Accuracy |
|--------|----------|
| NVDA   | 64.7%    |
| GOOGL  | 63.3%    |
| MSFT   | 62.1%    |
| META   | 61.9%    |
| AAPL   | 61.2%    |
| AMZN   | 60.8%    |
| TSLA   | 58.4%    |

## Stack

- **ML:** PyTorch, Hugging Face Transformers (FinBERT), scikit-learn
- **Data:** yfinance, ta (technical analysis)
- **API:** FastAPI + SQLite
- **Frontend:** Streamlit + Plotly
- **Deployment:** Docker + docker-compose
- **CI/CD:** GitHub Actions

## Features

- **Signal tab** — run prediction on any of 7 tickers with live price chart
- **Scan All tab** — analyze all 7 tickers simultaneously
- **History tab** — view all past predictions with distribution chart
- **Backtest tab** — per-ticker accuracy vs random baseline and academic benchmark

## Run With Docker

```bash
git clone https://github.com/ATURKIEH/stock-predictor
cd stock-predictor

# Generate model and scaler first
python pipeline.py

# Then run with Docker
docker-compose up --build
```

- FastAPI: http://localhost:8000/docs
- Streamlit: http://localhost:8501

## Run Locally

```bash
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\activate      # Windows
pip install -r requirements.txt
pip install torch==2.5.1 --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cpu

# Generate model
python pipeline.py

# Terminal 1
uvicorn app:app --reload

# Terminal 2
streamlit run streamlit_app.py
```

## API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| GET | `/health` | Health check |
| POST | `/predict` | Predict direction for a ticker |
| GET | `/predictions` | All past predictions |
| GET | `/predictions/{ticker}` | Predictions by ticker |

## Project Structure
stock-predictor/
├── stock_data.py      # StockData class — yfinance + technical indicators
├── sentiment.py       # SentimentAnalyzer class — FinBERT
├── model.py           # LSTMModel — PyTorch architecture
├── pipeline.py        # Training pipeline — data prep, training, evaluation
├── database.py        # Database class — SQLite
├── app.py             # FastAPI endpoints
├── streamlit_app.py   # Streamlit dashboard
├── Dockerfile
├── Dockerfile.streamlit
├── docker-compose.yml
└── .github/workflows/ci.yml

